figgy.title: Derrivates for TIFFs are not being generated for all images within one item after bulk ingest from Digital Studio server into Figgy
Volumes with collection membership show up as separate resources in DPUL

comments.body: Why are volumes also members of a collection?

@tpendragon I'm not sure if they were ingested as separate objects and then combined into a MVW, or if the ingest process added the collection membership at both levels. I edited the objects I was working with to remove the volume-level collection membership and DPUL updated as expected.

Since it's no longer possible to do this using the UI, this is probably mostly a note for future debugging. It's possible there are other collections that predate the forms change, so maybe this ticket is really "run a script to identify any volumes with collection membership and remove it"

pulfalight.title: Collection - C0187 is coming into Aeon requests with no site association.

comments.body:
I can't figure out how this works in the old site. Maybe you can help @sdellis ?

https://findingaids.princeton.edu/collections/C0187/c00003 definitely requests a Site of RBSC, but the only physloc code is hsvm. That's populated from here:

https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/pulfa/blob/e8f383c4135948412fd0f0f88bfd73201f05e6a1/webapp/xsl/component2html.xsl#L359-L361

However, that function it calls pulls from 

https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/pulfa/blob/e8f383c4135948412fd0f0f88bfd73201f05e6a1/webapp/xsl/lib.xsl#L40-L50

via

https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/pulfa/blob/e8f383c4135948412fd0f0f88bfd73201f05e6a1/webapp/xsl/lib.xsl#L912-L915

There's no RBSC there for hsvm. I don't see any logic that like...sets a default value or anything.

I can make everything that's not mapped fall back to the RBSC site, I'd just like evidence that's the right behavior.
@sdellis https://findingaids.princeton.edu/collections/C0187/c00003 does right?
@ccleeton has said that things should just default to RBSC, so I'm gonna do that to close this ticket.
